===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|ἐσωτερικός||belonging to an inner circle}}, from {{m|grc|ἐσωτέρω||further inside}}, comparative of {{m|grc|ἔσω||within}}, from {{m|grc|ἐς}}, {{m|grc|εἰς||into}} (''esoteric'' originally referred to the secret teachings of Greek philosophers, versus public or [[exoteric]] ones).

